  # Online Healthcare Management System

A fully functional Java Swing + MySQL hospital management application with role-based access control and clean layered architecture.  
This project is open source and released under the **MIT License**.

---

## 🚀 About the Project

This system provides a complete healthcare management workflow, including:

- Role-based login (Admin / Doctor / Patient)
- Appointment booking & management
- Patient medical records handling
- Doctor availability & schedule view
- Admin control over accounts & configurations
- Clean separation using MVC + DAO + Service architecture

Suitable for:
- Students building real portfolio projects  
- Open-source contributors  
- Companies learning layered Java application design

---

## 🧠 Tech Stack

- **Java** (JDK 8 or 17)
- **Swing UI**
- **MySQL Database**
- **JDBC Connector**
- **Layered Design (MVC + DAO + Service)**

---

## 📁 Project Structure

healthcare-system/
│
├── sql/
│ └── healthcare_schema.sql
│
├── src/
│ └── com/healthcare/
│ ├── model/ # Entity classes (User, Patient, Doctor, etc.)
│ ├── dao/ # DAO Interfaces
│ │ └── impl/ # JDBC Implementations
│ ├── service/ # Business logic
│ │ └── impl/
│ ├── ui/ # Swing screens & panels
│ └── util/ # DB connection & utilities
│
└── lib/
└── mysql-connector-j.jar


---

## ⚙️ Setup & Running

### 1️⃣ Import into IntelliJ (or any IDE)
- Clone the project
- Open the folder in your Java IDE

### 2️⃣ Install JDBC Driver
If using JAR:
- Place `mysql-connector-j.jar` in `/lib`
- Add it as a project dependency

### 3️⃣ Create the Database
Run in MySQL Workbench:

```sql
SOURCE sql/healthcare_schema.sql;

4️⃣ Configure DB Credentials
private static final String URL = "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/healthcare_db";
private static final String USER = "root";
private static final String PASSWORD = "YOUR_PASSWORD";

5️⃣ Run the Application
public static void main(String[] args) {
    new LoginFrame().setVisible(true);
}

🔐 Default Login (Sample)
| Role    | Email                                               | Password   |
| ------- | --------------------------------------------------- | ---------- |
| Admin   | [admin@hospital.com](mailto:admin@hospital.com)     | admin123   |
| Doctor  | [doctor1@hospital.com](mailto:doctor1@hospital.com) | doctor123  |
| Patient | [patient1@mail.com](mailto:patient1@mail.com)       | patient123 |

✔️ Key Features
Admin

Manage users

View all appointments

System configuration

Doctor

View patient appointments

Add/update medical reports

View ratings/feedback

Patient

Book appointments

View prescription history

Rate doctors

